<node CREATED="1664114550736" ID="ID_1807847393" MODIFIED="1675146372375">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(46, 63, 85); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)">
      <font size="3">The AUTOSAR Classic Platform architecture distinguishes on the highest abstraction level between three software layers which run on a microcontroller: application, runtime environment (RTE) and basic software (BSW). </font>
    </p>
    <ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 19px; margin-left: 17px; line-height: 26px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: rgb(46, 63, 85); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)">
      <li>
        <font size="3">The application software layer is mostly hardware independent. </font>
      </li>
      <li>
        <font size="3">Communication between software components and access to BSW via RTE. </font>
      </li>
      <li>
        <font size="3">The RTE represents the full interface for applications. </font>
      </li>
      <li>
        <font size="3">The BSW is divided in three major layers and complex drivers: </font>

        <ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 19px; margin-left: 17px; line-height: 26px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px">
          <li>
            <font size="3">Services, ECU (Electronic Control Unit) abstraction and microcontroller abstraction. (MCAL)</font>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        <font size="3">Services are divided furthermore into functional groups representing the infrastructure for system, memory and communication services </font>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
</node>
